    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Had to return the Airpods
    I ordered these a while ago, at first I thought they were great! I loved the noise cancelation, and really found them comfortable. A few months after I bought them the right Airpod sounded like something inside is becoming loose, baring in mind that I only use these for about 30/45 mins a day, only indoors so a very light use. Within the next 2 or 3 days the sound coming off that airpod was getting worse and worse.I contacted Amazon and had to send them away to see if they can be repaired or if they need replacement. The Airpods stayed with the approved service for over a week. I was then contacted and told they will send a new pair as these will take too long to repair and there is no point (makes you question how much the airpods actually cost to produce).A few days later I received the supposed replacement and it seemed all okay. Not even a month after receiving the replacement, the left airpod started malfunctioning. It was very obvious when I was using them on a call, and the left airpod was making all sorts of weird noises when I speak, so I suspect something had gone wrong with the microphone. A day or 2 later the right aipod started sounding like there is something that has gotten loose in them.I am content with the service I have received from Amazon when trying to resolve the issue.I have a pair of the normal airpods that I have been using for close to 5 years and have never had problems with using them day and night, rain or shine. The airpods pro didnt even last 1 year :(

    Oliver Longley
    5.0 out of 5 stars A really high quality pair of heaphones with some great features
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 7 February 2022
    Style Name: 1st Gen. MagSafe Charging CaseVerified Purchase
    I really love these headphones for every day use. They're small and convenient to carry around, they're quick to pair and unpair, and have great in-ear detection to autopause your music when removed.
    The case is simple, with a USB C or wireless charging capacity, a battery and charging indicator LED, and a useful feature that shows the battery of the case and buds when it is opened near your phone.

    The buds have really simple but effective inputs that can be easily configured. The defaults are single press for pause, double for skip, triple for backwards, and hold to change between transparency and noise cancelling modes. The buttons are light to press, but provide a satifying affirmative clicking feel when pressed. I much prefer the physical squeeze required rather than the side taps that my old Galaxy Buds Live had, this is because it is impossible to accidentally tap or tap too many times due to poor tap detection.

    The buds sport three unique modes for listening, alongside just plain output.
    -Active Noise Cancelling. This does a great job at blocking out background noise, and combined with the silicone ear tips allows a great fit, for passive noise cancelling.
    -Transparency Mode. This mode passes in noise from the outside, allowing better listening for traffic, conversations with the buds still in, and just listening to the outside world with music at the same time. I honestly can't believe how good this mode is at letting through everything at a sensible level, I can hear my footsteps as I walk, and the birds in the trees, but I can also hear traffic, all at the same time as my music. It is so well balanced, so I finally understand how Airpod users are having a conversation and forget they still have them in.
    -Spatial Audio. This mode makes it so that the audio is played through the buds corresponding to the direction you're facing from your device. This means that if your left bud is faced away from the device it will be quieter than the right bud faced towards the device. This mode is a cool gimmick that I suppose may be useful to get a more immersive film viewing experience.

    Overall the product is high quality, with great features.

    logan
    5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing, and suprisingly, well worth the money.
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 25 September 2022
    Style Name: 1st Gen. MagSafe Charging CaseVerified Purchase
    I took a massive risk with buying 185 earphones, this is way more than i'd typically like to spend.

    But i'd be damned, they're really, really good.

    The noise cancellation is fantastic, and really useful if you're a frequent user of public transport where things can get quite loud, once turned on all I can hear is my music.

    But by far the most impressive feature is the transparency mode. The ability to hear as if nothing was in your ears whatsoever is amazing, alongside features like conversation boost, which boosts the volume of the person you are currently facing, makes transparency mode a feature I never expected to be so good.

    Furthermore, audio quality is FANTASTIC absolutely no complaints from me there.

    It's worth noting that the Airpods Pro come with 3 ear-tips and none of which really fit me very well ( there's an option in settings for testing the fit) but I just stuck on the smallest tips and pushed them into my ears (obviously not being violent with it), and over a couple weeks or so of fairly-frequent use they just became more of a natural fit, and are much more comfortable now.

    So if at first, none of the eartips fit you, try a couple weeks just trying to make it work.

    JPF
    5.0 out of 5 stars Undisputed best convenience
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 18 May 2022
    Style Name: 1st Gen. MagSafe Charging CaseVerified Purchase
    Bought these to replace a first gen pair, which already had a round of replacements (one due to battery, other knocked out from my ear while leaving a crowded train). The battery was again busted in both, getting a replacement unfortunately would cost almost what Amazon is asking for the Pro's for, so went for it.

    The good:
    - fantastic convenience - for me, if you get a good fit, these are the definitive sports earbuds, they "just work" as much the first gen
    - sound quality is quite good - there is a critics bandwagon bashing these in terms of audio quality; I'm no audiophile, but I'm picky enough to tell the difference between a CD and lossy formats, and have to say I quite enjoy the sound and specially the bass on these ones, and also find the spatial audio and dolby atmos interesting; your mileage may vary, the quality of the seal you get hugely influences the sound on all headphones and specially earbuds, getting that wrong messes up the whole sound signature; regarding the treble, there is a trick someone found of going to Accessibility > Audio/Visual > Headphone Accommodations, then turn that on and select "Balanced Tone", that for me significantly improved the treble, kind of looks to me that Apple deliberately favours smoothing potentially harsh sounds over fidelity.

    The less good:
    - ANC is ok, miles away of the seal you get from let's say Sony WM-1000XM series over-ear headphones, I don't own Sony or Bose's earbuds to compare; I think is the most ANC people would want to safely walk around (probably better to turn it off altogether near traffic), but somewhat lacking for your typical open space office
    - larger case when compared with the first gen
    - more functions mean they are more complicated to use for less tech savvy people
    - more tightly coupled with Apple

    Over all, hands down recommendation if you have an iPhone, would be great if Apple supported these better on other platforms.
